Events.RelatedBody:
### Steps to Reproduce

1. Create a new Xamarin.iOS project
2. Open Info.plist and add the following lines:

```
    ...
    <key>firebase_crashlytics_collection_enabled</key>
    <true />
</dict>
```

3. Open csproj and add the following lines:

```
  ...
  <Import Project="$(MSBuildExtensionsPath)\Xamarin\iOS\Xamarin.iOS.CSharp.targets" />
  <!-- Update Info.plist values -->
  <Target Name="BeforeBuild">
      <PropertyListEditor PropertyList="Info.plist" Action="Set" Entry="firebase_crashlytics_collection_enabled" Type="bool" Value="false" />
  </Target>
</Project>
```

4. Try to build the app 

### Expected Behavior

App is built and Info.plist property is updated accordingly to `PropertyListEditor` parameters.

### Actual Behavior

Build fails with `error MT7067: Error saving 'Info.plist': Path is empty`.

